psychological disturbance,

13:43.910 --> 13:46.129
and the other can be solved by
half a glass of chardonnay.

13:49.741 --> 13:53.789
So the doctor prescribed Nizoral
and it blocked enzyme action,

13:53.833 --> 13:57.140
and the fungus
cleared right up.

13:57.184 --> 14:00.970
That's a very
disturbing picture.

14:01.014 --> 14:03.407
Yes, well, they say a picture's
worth a thousand words,

14:03.451 --> 14:06.236
but I say nothing beats a
picture and a thousand words.

14:06.280 --> 14:10.850
Still, you might want
to take it off Facebook.

14:10.893 --> 14:13.069
Oh, no. It's in my nature
to share.

14:13.113 --> 14:15.985
So, your turn.

14:16.029 --> 14:17.900
Uh, other than Amy,

14:17.944 --> 14:21.817
have you every had anything
removed from your body?

14:24.602 --> 14:27.736
I am not going to answer that.

14:27.779 --> 14:30.565
Smart. Save something for
our next get-together.

14:30.608 --> 14:33.437
Oh, we should commemorate
this one with a selfie.

14:36.745 --> 14:41.010
Oh, look at us,
two peas in a pod.

14:41.054 --> 14:42.751
Oh, speaking of vegetables,

14:42.794 --> 14:46.059
how about I start calling you
Old Lady Green Beans?

14:50.802 --> 14:52.892
Hey, you look
deep in thought.

14:52.935 --> 14:55.546
Ah, I'm just reflecting.About what?

14:55.590 --> 14:57.940
The first time
we slept together.

14:57.984 --> 15:00.725
Oh, honey. Don't beat
yourself up; it's great now.

15:02.989 --> 15:05.687
This is not good.

15:05.730 --> 15:06.993
Sheldon is hanging out
with my mom.

15:07.036 --> 15:08.342
Yeah. O-One sec.

15:08.385 --> 15:10.953
W-What do you mean,
"don't beat myself up"?

15:10.997 --> 15:13.086
AMY:
Guys, focus.

15:13.129 --> 15:15.131
My mom thinks
that Sheldon is the reason

15:15.175 --> 15:16.524
I don't spend a lot of time
with her.

15:16.567 --> 15:17.960
Well, why would
she think that?

15:18.004 --> 15:19.005
Because I told her.

15:19.048 --> 15:21.659
You need a cup of coffee?
Wake up!

15:21.703 --> 15:24.010
So you've been using Sheldon
as an excuse

15:24.053 --> 15:25.837
to get out of
seeing your mother?

15:25.881 --> 15:27.535
[sighs] I know.

15:27.578 --> 15:29.015
I feel terrible.

15:29.058 --> 15:31.669
I love my mom but,
you know, sometimes...

15:31.713 --> 15:34.672
Yeah. We-We've met her. Yeah.

15:34.716 --> 15:37.284
And it's easier to say
I can't spend time with her

15:37.327 --> 15:41.418
because of Sheldon than to admit
that I just, I don't want to.

15:41.462 --> 15:43.116
Totally understandable.

15:43.159 --> 15:44.813
I'll ask again,
what do you mean,

15:44.856 --> 15:46.815
"don't beat myself up"?

15:48.034 --> 15:50.993
And then you ask me 20
questions to try to determine

15:51.037 --> 15:53.300
which Nobel Prize-winning
physicist I am.

15:53.343 --> 15:54.866
Ready? Go.

15:58.609 --> 16:01.003
Can I give up?

16:01.047 --> 16:03.919
No. 19 questions left.

16:03.963 --> 16:05.965
[ringtone playing]

16:10.708 --> 16:11.971
Are you gonna get that?

16:12.014 --> 16:14.060
Oh, no. We're in the
middle of a game.

16:16.105 --> 16:18.978
18 questions left.

16:20.544 --> 16:22.285
Answer the phone,
Sheldon.

16:23.199 --> 16:25.071
Hello, Amy.

16:25.114 --> 16:26.898
Hey, how's it going?

16:26.942 --> 16:30.163
Well, Howard lured your dad away
with magic,

16:30.206 --> 16:31.991
so now I'm bonding
with your mom.

16:35.081 --> 16:36.996
I think she likes me.

16:39.302 --> 16:40.912
I'd like you a lot better

16:40.956 --> 16:43.176
if you weren't keeping
my daughter away from me.

16:43.219 --> 16:44.655
Uh, wh-- Hang on, Amy.

16:44.699 --> 16:47.528
What's the problem,
Green Beans?

16:47.571 --> 16:50.966
Amy said she couldn't come
to Thanksgiving dinner

16:51.010 --> 16:53.012
because you always have
to spend it with your mother.

16:53.055 --> 16:55.623
I haven't spent Thanksgiving
with my mother in years.

16:57.016 --> 16:58.365
Amy, why would you tell
your mother

16:58.408 --> 16:59.975
that I spend Thanksgiving
with my mother?

17:00.019 --> 17:03.022
Uh, no time
to talk about that now.

17:03.065 --> 17:04.936
All your action figures
are on fire.

17:04.980 --> 17:06.460
Harrison Ford's in the lobby.
Come quick.

17:10.072 --> 17:11.421
And Amy never joins us
for Sunday dinners

17:11.465 --> 17:13.641
because you refuse to go out
on a school night.

17:13.684 --> 17:16.165
Sh-- I can go out
on a school night

17:16.209 --> 17:18.515
as long as I'm in
my PJs by 10:00.

17:19.647 --> 17:21.083
Sheldon, don't listen to her.

17:21.127 --> 17:22.215
She doesn't know
what she's talking about.

17:22.258 --> 17:25.218
She's crazy!

17:25.261 --> 17:27.046
Hello, Amy.

17:28.960 --> 17:30.397
Hello, Mother.

17:33.139 --> 17:37.099
Great news. We-we can come
for Thanksgiving this year.

17:38.579 --> 17:40.581
I can't believe it.

17:40.624 --> 17:42.278
All this time
I've been angry at you

17:42.322 --> 17:43.888
when I should have
been angry at Amy.

17:43.932 --> 17:46.326
Look at that.
We're both angry at Amy.

17:46.369 --> 17:49.024
Maybe that's something
we could bond over.

17:50.156 --> 17:51.418
Let me ask you this:

17:51.461 --> 17:53.507
how do you feel about Howard?

17:53.550 --> 17:57.119
Oh, is he that odd little friend
you have with the haircut?

17:57.163 --> 18:00.601
I may have married
the wrong Fowler.

18:03.169 --> 18:06.737
Why would Amy feel
the need to lie to me?

18:06.781 --> 18:07.999
Well, perhaps because
you're her mother

18:08.043 --> 18:09.653
and she didn't want
to disappoint you.

18:09.697 --> 18:11.612
Really?

18:11.655 --> 18:13.701
Even after she threw you
under the bus,

18:13.744 --> 18:15.311
you're still
gonna defend her.

18:15.355 --> 18:16.965
Oh, yes.

18:17.008 --> 18:18.488
She's my wife
and I love her.

18:18.532 --> 18:20.795
And if I can forgive her for
putting ketchup on her eggs,

18:20.838 --> 18:23.145
I can forgive her for this.

18:23.189 --> 18:26.888
Her father does that,
it's disgusting.

18:26.931 --> 18:30.021
Amy's crazy,
you are a delight.

18:38.465 --> 18:40.206
Good morning.

18:40.249 --> 18:42.121
Mm. Good morning.

18:42.164 --> 18:43.339
I ordered some coffee for us.

18:43.383 --> 18:46.168
Oh, fantastic.

18:46.212 --> 18:47.996
[sighs]

18:48.039 --> 18:49.650
Last night was...

18:49.693 --> 18:51.391
wonderful.

18:53.044 --> 18:55.090
[sighs] But all we
did was talk.

18:55.134 --> 18:57.571
Yeah. And it was wonderful.

18:57.614 --> 18:59.921
Am I safe to assume
you talking to me now

18:59.964 --> 19:01.966
is a good sign
for our marriage?

19:02.010 --> 19:04.230
[chuckles] Yeah,
and-and for my liver.

19:06.188 --> 19:07.624
Hey, about the other thing.

19:07.668 --> 19:09.496
Um...

19:09.539 --> 19:11.933
Should we just wait
for another night?

19:13.239 --> 19:16.459
Or I go take a shower,

19:16.503 --> 19:18.896
and you decide how
you want to play this.

19:24.772 --> 19:27.166
Take a shower with me, Raj.

19:35.826 --> 19:37.176
Thank you, Amy.

19:37.219 --> 19:38.655
It's so nice of you
to have us over for dinner.

19:38.699 --> 19:42.616
[chuckles] Couldn't think
of a single reason not to.

19:42.659 --> 19:45.053
Yeah, and boy,
did she try.

19:45.096 --> 19:47.011
Thank you, honey.

19:47.055 --> 19:48.187
Oh, you're welcome, dear.

19:49.797 --> 19:52.103
Would anyone like to see the
magic trick Howard taught me?

19:52.147 --> 19:54.845
I'd love to see your trick,
Daddy.

19:58.197 --> 20:01.243
A perfectly ordinary
table knife.

20:01.287 --> 20:02.940
[exhales]

20:05.291 --> 20:07.467
Watch closely.

20:07.510 --> 20:09.730
Voilà.

20:09.773 --> 20:13.124
Oh, my gosh,
that was so good.

20:18.782 --> 20:21.481
Well, look,
there's fake blood, too.

20:23.352 --> 20:25.049
I'll be right back.

20:29.489 --> 20:32.056
I don't know about you,
but I don't really like magic.

20:32.100 --> 20:36.322
You just keep getting
better and better.

